The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 In step with Manipuri

 Under the aegis of EZCC, renowned classical Manipuri danseuse Darshana Jhaveri (picture left) conducted a workshop from August 1 to 9. This evenings dance recitals by its participants begin with analytical or basic movements demonstrating the characteristic styles of Manipuri in its lasya and tandava aspects. The students also present Maibi Jagoi, the traditional dance of maibis (priestesses) during the festival of Laiharaoba. Other performances include Brahmatal Prabandha, an item comprising a group of tala compositions on tal duytal macha, tal brahmatal, tal tanchep and tal menkup in tandava style, and Khubakishei, a clap-dance performed on the occasion of Rathayatra in Manipur. To be followed by Shukasaridwanda by Darshana Jhaveri, which enacts a lovers? quarrel between two parrots, Shuka and Sari. The programme concludes with Bhanusingher Padavali, a dance-drama presented by the students of Manipuri Nartanalaya, choreographed and directed by Kalavati Devi.

 Event: Manipuri dance recital

 When: Today at 6 pm

 Where: Bharatiyam Cultural Multiplex, IB 201 Salt Lake




